# tinyproxy DENY list (FilterExtended regex, FilterDefaultDeny No = default allow).
# Empirical blocklist of places a Jane Street puzzle solution could exist.
# Matched against the CONNECT host. Anything not listed is ALLOWED (agents may
# consult math/programming reference material). Every request is logged; the
# post-hoc transcript audit is the backstop for anything that slips through.
#
# --- the source itself ---
(^|\.)janestreet\.com$
#
# --- code hosts (solver repos: gowen100, miguelbper, iamzr, ...) ---
(^|\.)github\.com$
(^|\.)githubusercontent\.com$
(^|\.)github\.io$
(^|\.)gist\.github\.com$
(^|\.)gitlab\.com$
(^|\.)bitbucket\.org$
(^|\.)codeberg\.org$
(^|\.)sourceforge\.net$
(^|\.)gitea\.io$
#
# --- search engines (the discovery layer: block the ability to FIND a
#     solution page even on an otherwise-allowed host) ---
(^|\.)google\.[a-z.]+$
(^|\.)bing\.com$
(^|\.)duckduckgo\.com$
(^|\.)yandex\.[a-z.]+$
(^|\.)baidu\.com$
(^|\.)search\.brave\.com$
(^|\.)ecosia\.org$
(^|\.)startpage\.com$
(^|\.)qwant\.com$
(^|\.)search\.marginalia\.nu$
(^|\.)searx\.
(^|\.)kagi\.com$
(^|\.)you\.com$
(^|\.)perplexity\.ai$
(^|\.)phind\.com$
#
# --- video / social / blog hubs where writeups & walkthroughs live ---
(^|\.)youtube\.com$
(^|\.)youtu\.be$
(^|\.)reddit\.com$
(^|\.)redd\.it$
(^|\.)twitter\.com$
(^|\.)x\.com$
(^|\.)medium\.com$
(^|\.)substack\.com$
(^|\.)quora\.com$
#
# --- puzzle / Q&A sites that host Jane Street solutions specifically ---
(^|\.)puzzling\.stackexchange\.com$
#
# --- other LLM/assistant endpoints (avoid outsourcing the solve) ---
(^|\.)openai\.com$
(^|\.)googleapis\.com$
(^|\.)generativelanguage\.googleapis\.com$
(^|\.)deepseek\.com$
(^|\.)mistral\.ai$
